WorldStage Newsonline– An Executive Director of  Vitafoam Nigeria Plc,  a foam manufacturing company based in Ikeja, Lagos, Mr Adeniyi Taiwo Ayodele has been reported to have purchased 192,000  units of the company at the Nigerian Stock Exchange on 21st August, 2020. A notice signed Mr Olalekan Sanni, Company Secretary/Legal Adviser on August 31, 2020 confirmed that the stocks were purchased at N5.22 per share which translated to N1,002,240. Vitafoam is one of Nigeria’s largest foam manufacturers, producing both flexible and rigid polyurethane products. The company also owns interest in Vitafoam Ghana and Vitafoam Sierra Leone.